# Component Reuse Guidelines

## Always Prefer Existing Components
- Before creating new components, check if existing atoms/molecules can be reused
- Look for similar functionality in [atoms](mdc:apps/web/src/presentation/components/atoms/) and [molecules](mdc:apps/web/src/presentation/components/molecules/)
- Compose complex components from simpler existing ones

## Component Hierarchy
- **Atoms**: Basic UI elements (Button, Input, Label, etc.)
- **Molecules**: Combinations of atoms (SearchInput, PriceRange, etc.)
- **Organisms**: Complex components (FiltersBar, PropertyCard, etc.)

## Reuse Strategy
1. Check existing components first
2. If functionality is 80% similar, extend existing component
3. If completely different, create new component
4. Always export new components in appropriate index files

## Examples of Good Reuse
- Use existing `Input` component instead of creating new input
- Use existing `Button` component for all buttons
- Compose complex forms from existing form atoms
- Reuse `Label` component for all labels

## Anti-patterns to Avoid
- Creating duplicate components with similar functionality
- Not checking existing components before creating new ones
- Hardcoding styles instead of using existing component variants